quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  50,30,"On that Day We will say to Hell, \"Are you filled (to the full)?\", and it will say, \"Are there (yet) more (to come)"
  50,31,"And Paradise will be brought near for the God-revering, pious; not (any longer) is it far"
  50,32,"This is what was promised for you – for everyone who was penitent, careful in keeping his duties (to God)"
  50,33,"Everyone who stood in awe of the All-Merciful though unseen (beyond their perception), and has come with a heart contrite and devout"
  50,34,Now enter it in peace (secure from any trouble or distress). That is the Day of immortality
  50,35,"Therein will be for them everything that they desire, and in Our Presence there is yet more"
  50,36,"How many a generation We have destroyed before them who were mightier than these in prowess, and overran other lands. But was there any place of escape (for them when God’s punishment became due: is there ever)"
  50,37,"Surely in that is a warning reminder for anyone who has a heart (that is truly alive), and who gives ear (to the one conveying this reminder), with eyes able to see well"
  50,38,"We assuredly created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them in six days, and nothing of fatigue touched us"
  50,39,So (with confident reliance on Our promise and Power) bear with patience whatever they say and glorify your Lord with His praise before the rising of the sun and before its setting
  50,40,"And during (some part of) the night, too, glorify Him, and after the prostrations"
  50,41,And wait with ears able to hear for the Day when the Caller will call out from a place near
  50,42,The Day when they will hear the Blast in truth (as a predetermined decree of God that must happen). That is the Day of the coming forth (when the dead will be raised from their graves)
  50,43,"Surely it is We Who give life and cause to die, and to Us is the homecoming"
  50,44,"That Day the earth will be rent asunder away from them, and they, hurrying out of it (will come to the gathering). That will be a gathering easy for Us"
  50,45,"We know best whatever they say, and you (O Messenger) are not one to compel them (to faith). So remind and warn by the Qur’an him who fears My threat"